Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.50,0:00:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Glory and excelsis Deo.\NGlory be to thee, O Lord, most high.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.88,0:00:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,With those words, we set the energy for the group\Nand for all of us forevermore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.83,0:00:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if it's forevermore.\NWith that, we set the energy for our future forevermore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.67,0:00:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NForevermore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.22,0:00:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Forevermore.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.35,0:00:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, having taken care of the future,\Nnow we'll have to turn our attention to the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.78,0:00:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, today is a wondrous day.\NWe have all our friends from Korea and Dr. Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.07,0:01:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Say hello, Dr. Moon.\NShe's the head of the Radhaswami Retreat Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.04,0:01:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that correct?\NDo I have it correctly?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.70,0:01:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NRadhaswami?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.76,0:01:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that correct?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.54,0:01:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NShe knows if she says no, she gets a blow, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.70,0:01:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we went to Korea for several years.\NAnd Dr. Moon took care of us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.98,0:01:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a wondrous trip and spoke via translator there.\NSo today we will speak in both English and Korean.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.56,0:01:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here are from Korea?\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.87,0:01:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm from Korea.\NI'm from Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.07,0:02:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm from Korea because I've been there twice, so it'll be somewhat unique today, very interesting\Nfor all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.13,0:02:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Korean people were extremely hospitable to us when we were there.\NAnd I remember, if you're a spiritual teacher, you're treated somewhat differently in a way
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.13,0:02:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because I said, gee, I don't have any Diet Pepsi.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.81,0:02:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NWell, the word that I didn't have any Diet Pepsi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.12,0:02:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty-six.\NTwenty-six.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.78,0:02:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty-six people spread out over the whole big city of Seoul and searched the entire city.\NAnd by God, in a warehouse somewhere, they found some Diet Pepsi in the back of this warehouse and brought it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.97,0:02:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the day was saved.\NTwenty-six people searching for a Diet Pepsi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.86,0:03:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's the reverence with which they hold a teacher.\NAnd I felt very honored by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.06,0:03:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty-six people.\NTwenty-six people searched for a Diet Pepsi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.22,0:03:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also learned never to appreciate anything because if you hesitate and appreciate by something,\Nthey want to go and buy it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.77,0:03:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,One time I looked at a Buddha, and, you know, it was an antique Buddha, and it was a beautiful Buddha.\NAnd I looked at it like, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.77,0:03:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I walked away, and I noticed Dr. Moon is dickering with the owner of the store.\NShe's got to spend $6.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.12,0:03:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got to spend $6,000 for this antique Buddha.\NSo I learned never look like you'll appreciate something because they're going to have to get it for you, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:04:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was the style of life there and the way they greet each other, you know, in such a genteel culture.\NSo you get spoiled being in such a genteel culture and coming back to one that is really far more crude.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.12,0:04:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh...\NHa, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.37,0:04:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.78,0:04:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.86,0:04:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.90,0:04:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.93,0:04:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.97,0:04:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.02,0:04:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.08,0:04:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.19,0:04:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.25,0:04:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.25,0:04:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.59,0:04:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.71,0:04:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NHa, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.24,0:04:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.\NUnbelievable what goes on in the public domain nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will, uh...\NUh, start, we will first present what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.56,0:04:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...\NNow we have a translator.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.39,0:04:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your name?\NUh, my name is Daho Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.07,0:04:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Daho Lee.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.04,0:04:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to say it again?\NUh, Daho Lee.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.13,0:04:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Da...\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.69,0:04:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Daho means, uh, large lake, great lake.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.77,0:04:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NThat's meaning...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.06,0:04:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NAll right, so today will be a little different than usual, which means it will be the same as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When do I start translating?\NI'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.13,0:05:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I forgot.\NI forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.24,0:05:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That shows your silly, silly me.\NSilly me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.62,0:05:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you say that?\NSilly me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.17,0:05:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't say that.\NWell, we prepared to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.30,0:05:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to go through the presentation of the material to cover the basics,\Nso that the most important things that I want you to be sure to know and be familiar with will become second nature to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.74,0:05:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first slide we have is always the scale of consciousness,\Nwhich today we...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.56,0:05:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have in both English and Korean.\NSo we're ready for that slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.36,0:06:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it took me quite a while to write this part here.\NIt took me quite a while to write this part here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.01,0:06:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it's legible from the audience.\NBut as you can see, on the left, we have the scale of consciousness in English,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.29,0:06:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and on the right, we have it in Korean.\NAlso, it's a guide to consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.35,0:06:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the left, it's in Korean.\NYeah, very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.06,0:06:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if this one...\NI don't know if this one right here is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.25,0:06:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It needs to be over a little bit, but...\NIt'll do for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.43,0:06:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll do for now.\NWell, we were in Korea, the people were...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.12,0:07:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were in Korea, the people were extremely gracious.\NAnd if you go to Korea too often, you get spoiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.24,0:07:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you come back to the States, you're upset because people are not bowing to you when you meet them.\NSo their culture has a certain graciousness to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.22,0:07:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Graciousness that is lacking in many other cultures.\NAnd that's why Korea has always had a special place in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.06,0:08:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. So even when you walk by a stranger, they go like so, like in a hotel lobby, you know, you meet somebody.\NAnd the strangers all greet each other thusly. Isn't that beautiful? A way to live?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.80,0:08:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is a need to the Korean culture, a charm, a charm.\NA charm, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.19,0:08:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Charm, yeah, yeah.\NI got it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.86,0:09:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to import a lot of Korean people.\NTo teach America the graciousness of living.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.54,0:09:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, yeah, to offset the aggressiveness.\NSo, yeah, without the grace, the aggressiveness becomes imbalanced, it becomes overly aggressive, and the ship falls over this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.54,0:09:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, and Korea is very successful because it also is assertive and, you know, it's not wishy-washy.\NSo this doesn't mean wishy-washy, just says you better be careful because God will get you if you don't.
