Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.75,0:10:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,것들은 곧 될 것입니다.\NSo we're very happy. We're very happy that the books are available to the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.49,0:11:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,우리는 한국인들에게 한국어로 책이 전해지고 있다는 것이 매우 행복합니다.\NSo we will present a sequence of slides that covers the basics, and then the presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will be translated into Korean right away. So you won't have to wait for the Korean\Ntranslation. It will follow immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.14,0:11:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\N기본적인 것들을 커버하기 위해서 계속 시리즈의 슬라이드를 보여드릴 것이고
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.72,0:11:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,한국말로 바로 트랜슬레이션 해드리겠습니다.\NSo here, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.20,0:11:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll go to...\NLet's go to slide number one, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.27,0:11:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the slides.\N첫 번째 슬라이드를 보겠습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.48,0:11:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Not number one, but the first one.\NWhere is the slide lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.89,0:11:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is she?\NWell, no, I've got them circled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.41,0:11:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Whichever one, they're circled, right?\NOkay, we'll go through the circled list.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.00,0:12:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,동그라미로 표시된 것부터 해주십시오.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.66,0:12:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the map of consciousness in English, and you see it combines the way you view\NGod, the way you view yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.57,0:12:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that determines how you experience life.\NIt determines what emotions tend to predominate, and then we give it, in terms of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.10,0:12:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,research, the name of the process.\NSo we see that the enlightened states begin with honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.91,0:12:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They really begin with honesty, and that moves up to trust, and then optimism.\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.12,0:12:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I forgot the translator.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.27,0:12:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I can do this.\NOh, well, we'll get around to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.08,0:12:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness.\NEeyore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.10,0:13:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThis is the map of consciousness in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.67,0:13:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,On the right, you see how you view God, and how you view yourself, and the levels that\Nsuit you, and how emotions are expressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.29,0:13:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are the things.\NBut you need to really calculate that you know who you are and what can affect what
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.76,0:13:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you are.\NSo despite the fact that there are a number of new words being read or exa illustrated
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.27,0:13:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,on the wide screen on the website, you'll never know that you're going to be a hero if\Nsomebody got caught up in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.88,0:13:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt's hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.92,0:13:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...\NThere are several.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.76,0:13:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try to do them all.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.80,0:13:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, then.\NYes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.47,0:13:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the question was what you actually think about self, about others.\NWell, we're supposed to see something from the gears because there's nothing to get behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.59,0:14:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Each person, when they're born, is born with a certain level of consciousness.\NThat's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.67,0:14:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Each person already has a calibrated level of consciousness at the moment of birth.\NSo how could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.10,0:14:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And that brings in the whole subject of karma.\NYes. And Westerners tend to think of karma as an Eastern philosophic position
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.19,0:15:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and not an experiential reality.\NConsciousness research, however, shows that it is an important fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.38,0:15:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact. It's not just a theory.\NConsciousness research is not just a theory. It's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.99,0:15:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that karma is extremely important.\NAnd the whole purpose of human life is to undo negative karma and acquire positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.14,0:15:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma is very important.\NAnd the most important thing in human life is to get rid of negative karma and get positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.16,0:15:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That is true. Resist.\NThat is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.01,0:16:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If the arm says it's true, it's true.\NI refer to her as the arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.16,0:16:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you want to see if a thing is true or not,\Nshe merely holds out her arm and I press down with two fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.50,0:16:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I press down moderately. Resist.\NAnd I say resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.64,0:16:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If what I'm holding in mind is true, her arm goes strong.\NIf it is false, her arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.50,0:16:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This is impersonal.\NIt's the reaction of protoplasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.74,0:17:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is pro-life. Pro-life supports life.\NAnd falsehood is that which is anti-life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.77,0:17:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is a primitive reaction that starts way back at the level of protozoa.\NSo it's built into the proto-planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.60,0:17:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If primitive life could not discern good from bad,\Nif primitive life could not discern good from bad,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.90,0:17:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it would soon die of poisoning itself.\NThe first thing an organism needs to know is this good
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.69,0:17:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and supports life.\NOr is it bad and will kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.88,0:18:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing to know is this good and supports life.\NOr is it bad and will kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.59,0:18:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the first thing to know.\NSo this response is inborn, right from the level of protozoa,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.76,0:18:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,onto human life.\NThe reaction to this truth is inborn to the protozoa as well as to humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.65,0:18:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's built because\Nthe expressions of life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.07,0:18:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are expressions of levels of\Nwell, that's too complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's built into the infinite field\Nof consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.48,0:18:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the human,\Nthis is individual consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.59,0:19:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the animal,\Nit's group consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.85,0:19:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.68,0:19:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the animals\Nall share one
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.33,0:19:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NThe animals all share one consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.44,0:19:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And humans have\Nindividual consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.57,0:19:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what one bird knows,\Nwhat one bird knows,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.85,0:19:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,all the birds know.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's interesting.\NThere are many
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:20:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,explanations for this\Nphenomenon of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.77,0:20:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,truth versus falsehood.\NTruth makes your arm go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.13,0:20:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood makes your arm go weak.\NTruth makes your arm go strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.50,0:20:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And falsehood makes your arm go weak.\NThere are many explanations
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.20,0:20:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for this reaction.\NThis happens if you believe in God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.03,0:20:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you believe in God,\Nthen your arm will go strong
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.00,0:20:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with truth\Nand weak with falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.02,0:20:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you deny God,\Nif you're an atheist
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.16,0:20:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and deny God,\Nthis will not work for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.98,0:20:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that strange?\NSo, those who deny
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.85,0:21:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of truth\Nare denied the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.46,0:21:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,benefit of knowing the truth.\NSo, to do this test,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.24,0:21:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you need two people\Nthat are integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.53,0:21:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Two people that themselves\Ncalibrate over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.33,0:21:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,are integrous.\NIn order to do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.05,0:21:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you need more than 200 people\Nwho are of a full level.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.33,0:21:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, after we wrote about this,\Nthere were various professors,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.61,0:21:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,professors at universities and all,\Nwho said it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.71,0:21:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, after we wrote about this,\Nthere were various professors, professors at universities and all, who said it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.86,0:21:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, after we wrote about this,\Nthere were various professors, professors at universities and all, who said it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.86,0:21:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When we did our research,\Nthere many professors over at the university
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.10,0:21:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and people like that\Nclaimed that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.82,0:22:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this doesn't actually work.\NThen, we found out
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.25,0:22:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they were all atheists.\NThen, we found out
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.46,0:22:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are all atheists.\NThen, we found out
