Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.34,0:41:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,if conditions allow\Nthey appear like this
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.96,0:41:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't appear out of nowhere\Nand do they potentially leave pieces behind
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.44,0:41:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,they are 했는데\Nnot by some mother nature
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.67,0:41:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but by something\Nthey appear out of nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.13,0:41:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to do the divinity\Nbut that's not the point
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.65,0:41:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's not sleep\Nnow I didn't cause him to move away
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.34,0:41:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,did I\Ndidn't
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.90,0:41:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so what we see\Nbecause of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.40,0:41:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine creation\Ncomes out from nowhere
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.76,0:42:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so what we see\Nbecause of the divine creation
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.96,0:42:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is the emergence of potentiality\Ninto in actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.88,0:42:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,when the local conditions\Nare appropriate
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.88,0:42:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how everything happens\NWhen there's enough moisture, enough sun, this becomes that, because it's fulfilling its creative potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.46,0:42:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see...\NYeah, yeah, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.11,0:42:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the creation of the holy spirit, the potential appears in reality.\NSo what we witness is the unfolding of creation from potentiality into actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.84,0:43:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When the local conditions are favorable, the potentiality emerges as a manifestation of its potential.\NWhen conditions are favorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.71,0:43:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we do gardening, we put water and fertilizer so the local conditions will be favorable that the seed will grow roots and grow as corn.\NSo we have the right conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.55,0:44:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and so then the karmic dominance that prevails, without karmic dominance of our fields, we wouldn't be here together this morning.\NYou have the karmic propensity to be here, and I have the propensity to be here, and so the actuality is the two of us standing here together.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.59,0:44:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.30,0:44:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.30,0:44:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.30,0:44:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.30,0:44:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.30,0:44:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.30,0:44:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.30,0:44:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.30,0:44:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.30,0:44:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.30,0:44:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.30,0:44:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.30,0:44:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.30,0:44:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.30,0:44:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.30,0:44:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.30,0:44:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.03,0:44:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.03,0:44:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.03,0:44:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.03,0:44:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.03,0:44:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.03,0:44:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.15,0:44:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.15,0:44:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.15,0:44:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.15,0:44:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.15,0:44:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.15,0:44:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.26,0:44:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.26,0:44:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.26,0:45:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.11,0:45:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In that instant is the unfolding of the creation as it's presenting itself at this moment.\NEvolutionary we call that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.88,0:45:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all of the life is divine, innately divine.\NAll of creation is divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.13,0:46:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's go back to the scale of consciousness.\NAnd you see at consciousness, as the consciousness level goes up, you see this is illumination.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.07,0:46:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At level 600, you begin to see the divinity of all that exists.\NAt level 600, you begin to see the divinity of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.30,0:46:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The world becomes increasingly beautiful.\NNow, the beauty of life cannot be seen from down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.65,0:46:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here, life is horrible, painful.\NSad, frightening, frustrating, infuriating.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.46,0:47:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For people below 200 live in a miserable world.\NYeah, you cannot make them happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.86,0:47:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhen people think, oh, if I had a lot of money, I'd be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.17,0:47:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So research has been done on people who win great prizes.\NYou know, like, what kind of...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.55,0:47:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Lottery?\NLottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.28,0:47:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NLottery?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.48,0:47:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NLottery?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.48,0:47:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Lottery.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.48,0:47:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Lottery.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.48,0:47:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NLottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.48,0:47:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NLottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.48,0:48:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there's only one thing you can oppress, and it's\Nseeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.28,0:48:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So pray to the Lord\Nthat you will not be lucky
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.84,0:48:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and win the lottery.\NNothing worse could be
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.80,0:48:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for you in this world.\NIt's sad news
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.25,0:48:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,if you win a million dollars\Nunexpectedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.09,0:48:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to call\Nthe undertaker
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.13,0:48:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and arrange things\Nin advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.48,0:48:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right,\Nso spiritual endeavor
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.15,0:48:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then is really\Nthe technique
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.82,0:49:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by which\Nwe transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.55,0:49:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this level,\Nwe transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.42,0:49:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,these levels.\NAnd of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.75,0:49:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they're all calibratable\Nnumerically
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.61,0:49:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,just for convenience.\NSo we work
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.11,0:49:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,through forgiveness\Nand we work
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.57,0:49:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of anger\Nand resentment
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.61,0:49:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these things.\NWe work through forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.96,0:49:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and we go through neutral.\NNeutral is very comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.38,0:49:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell people\Nif you despair
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.25,0:49:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,about these things,\Ngo for neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.90,0:49:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stay neutral.\NNo attractions,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.30,0:50:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,no aversions.\NWhoever wins the election,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.11,0:50:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay.\NYeah, it's okay either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.59,0:50:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The country will survive.\NYeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.57,0:50:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we move up a little higher to willingness, which is more optimistic.\NAnd we work up to acceptance, which is based on forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.67,0:50:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Course of Miracles, here's the power of the Course of Miracles,\Nis the willingness to forgive everything and everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.30,0:51:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you're willing to forgive everything and anyone, the world begins to look different.\NAnd it opens the way, eventually, for reverence.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.65,0:51:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is why I like the Korean lifestyle.\NWhen you go like so, you're showing reverence for life, reverence for your fellow man,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.55,0:51:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,reverence for your creator, reverence for...\NFor your country. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.17,0:51:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A beautiful way to live in the world of reverence.\NSo when you try to forgive anyone and everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.11,0:51:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the world begins to look different.\NAnd then you start to have a sense of reverence for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.15,0:51:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You start to have a sense of respect for the country and the God.\NYou start to have a sense of respect for the country and the God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.96,0:51:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Dr. Kim, you like Korean culture.\NAnd you like Korean culture, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.46,0:52:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you like Korean culture, because you respect each other and express your respect for each other.\NAll right. So with spiritual practice,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.23,0:52:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,one experiences oneself and the world differently,\Nand it appears differently, it looks different.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.80,0:52:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Through spiritual practice,\Npeople experience themselves differently,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.94,0:52:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and they view themselves differently.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.57,0:52:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially to be loving towards all that exists.\NPeople say, what can I do to help the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.92,0:52:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't help their own garage, but they're going to save the world, don't they?\NGarage?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.21,0:53:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to move ahead in consciousness is to be loving towards all that exists.\NTo be as benign and loving as you can be towards all of life and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.40,0:53:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The love is a different love.\NA spiritual love is not personal and it's not an attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.26,0:54:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We can appreciate. One form of love is appreciation.\NSo, the people who set off bombs around the world and kill innocent people,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.55,0:54:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they do that out of a belief system that somehow they're serving God by doing this.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.71,0:54:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,their brain wants to believe\Nthat their job is to kill all people who don't believe the way they believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.63,0:54:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's true. They may kill you.\NSo, should we hate them?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.07,0:54:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.50,0:55:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The little lion will kill you.\NBecause the little lion loves you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.53,0:55:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The little lion loves you.\NSo, the little lion will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.07,0:55:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the little lion will kill you.\NAnd therefore, he eats you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.65,0:55:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we can love even the lion that eats your cat and your dog.\NI came front to front with a cougar very recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.09,0:56:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked out my kitchen window and here was a cougar walking right past my kitchen window.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.50,0:56:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As a doggie, come in here.\NHa ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.92,0:56:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha.\NIt's a very big, uh, it's a very big cat, but it's five, six feet long.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.76,0:56:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'd be happy to eat you, I'm sure.\NSo, I respect the mountain lion.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.88,0:56:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I respect him.\NSo, respect is a different kind of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.76,0:56:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You sonn.\NSo, God created the cougar?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.82,0:56:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWell, he created evolution, and evolution created the cougar.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.82,0:56:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in court, God is responsible.\NHa ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.69,0:57:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha.\NUh, God created Cougars, and God created shelves.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.21,0:57:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Cougar eats you.\NSo, Cougar eats you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.53,0:57:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Cougar eats you.\Nnot make you happy
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.23,0:57:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but it will make\Nthe cougar happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.32,0:57:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I'm careful\Nwhen I let the dog out.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.44,0:57:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I look outside first\Nmake sure there's no
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.55,0:57:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So being loving\Ndoes not mean being stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.53,0:57:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes people\Nmisunderstand
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.34,0:57:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal love\Nand they think
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.53,0:57:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that they should be\Nhospitable
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.90,0:57:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to the cougar\Nin their own backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.84,0:58:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you have a dog\Nit's not wise
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.82,0:58:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to invite a cougar\Nto live in your backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.25,0:58:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the world\Nwe live today
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.26,0:58:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we live in a world\Nin which conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.07,0:58:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,arises\Nas an impersonal
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.19,0:58:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of evolution.\NSo divine evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.30,0:59:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,results in the creation\Nof benign
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.71,0:59:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,friendly people\Nand also
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.03,0:59:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,warlike people.\NSo divine evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.94,0:59:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,results in the creation\Nof very gentle
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.59,0:59:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and loving people.\NSo in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.84,0:59:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,there are places in the world\Nwhere the people believe
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.26,0:59:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that to serve God\Nthey must kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.42,0:59:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing you is serving God.\NIn what part of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.09,0:59:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They think that\Nin the world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.15,0:59:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there are whole areas\Nthat think
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.92,0:59:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that the way to serve God\Nis to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.21,0:59:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the world\Nthere are places
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.42,0:59:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,where people believe\Nthat the way to serve God
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.42,1:00:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is to kill you.\NSo I respect
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.84,1:00:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that belief\Nbut I do not want
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.96,1:00:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,them living in my backyard.\NSo in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.05,1:00:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,there are people\Nwho are also misguided
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.17,1:00:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,who think the way\Nto handle it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.30,1:00:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is to enjoy it.\NSo in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.67,1:00:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there are people\Nwho think the way
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.67,1:00:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to invite mountain lions\Nto live in your backyard.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.21,1:00:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So people who are\Nmisguided
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.53,1:00:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,think it is right\Nto invite a small cat
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.05,1:00:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to your yard.\NTheir idea is
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.50,1:00:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they will change\Nthe nature of the cougar
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.38,1:00:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,who will then become\Nyour friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.80,1:00:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be your friend.\NHe'll purify you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.92,1:01:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll eat you.\NSo that takes care
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.13,1:01:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the political tensions\Nof the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.05,1:01:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It only took us\Na couple of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.88,1:01:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy.\NLet everything be
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.42,1:01:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is\Nbut respect it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.98,1:01:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to respect\Nthe mountain lion
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.40,1:01:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't need\Nto respect it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.23,1:01:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point\Nto hate him.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.82,1:01:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point\Nto hate the mountain lion.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.88,1:01:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But you also remember\Nhe will be glad
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.78,1:01:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to eat you.\NSo spirituality
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.11,1:01:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be also\Nhandled with
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.53,1:01:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,reason and logic.\NSpirituality
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.80,1:01:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be also\Nhandled with
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.46,1:01:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,reason and logic.\NSo faith is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.23,1:02:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,bulwarked.\NSo faith is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.28,1:02:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,reinforced by reason.\NSo faith is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.65,1:02:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,reinforced by reason.\NFaith and reason
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.92,1:02:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,go hand in hand.\NFaith and reason
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.73,1:02:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,go hand in hand.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.98,1:02:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.57,1:02:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is\Na lot of talky talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.00,1:02:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move to the next one.\NWe have five minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.15,1:02:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What? We have five minutes left.\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.92,1:02:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NIs everything I said
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.80,1:02:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,simple and obvious?\NIs it okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.40,1:02:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnybody got any objections
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.30,1:02:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or questions?\NWant to jump up and become indignant?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.63,1:02:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.\NI want it my way.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.09,1:03:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo the trick is to make God's way
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.13,1:03:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,your way.\NSo what we have to do is
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.21,1:03:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,create God's way\Ninto our own way.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.03,1:03:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think the way\Nto do it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.01,1:03:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,without having to go to church\Nis to be gracious
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.76,1:03:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and loving towards all of life.\NThat will save you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.51,1:03:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go to church.\NIf you love
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.42,1:03:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,everything in life\Nyou exist,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.67,1:03:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need to go to church.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.44,1:03:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, to me, spiritual then means an overall attitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.55,1:03:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being in the world.\NIt isn't what you do, it isn't what you say, it isn't what you buy, it isn't what you sell.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.78,1:04:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, spiritual is a general attitude.\NIt's the way you are in the world, it's the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.23,1:04:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way you are is a consequence of that which you have become.\NSo, it's not what you do, it's not what you say, it's what you are that changes the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.28,1:04:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I will see you after the break.\NHow long do we have?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.59,1:05:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What you are changes the world.\NOkay, we will resume, God willing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.86,1:05:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We were just recalling our trips to Korea.\NYou can all sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.07,1:05:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Our trips to Korea, because of the change of the international date line,\Nour booking agent made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.07,1:05:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The plane we were supposed to catch left the day before.\NThere we were in San Francisco airport, no plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.30,1:05:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold and windy, and you can't flag down a taxi cab in the airport, it's against the law.\NSo, in the cold, dark wind, having missed the plane,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.65,1:05:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to charge a couple of blocks down to get a telephone and call a taxi cab to come and get me.\NBut we love the Korean people so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.21,1:06:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if they would all just move closer, it would be fine.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.40,1:06:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.51,1:06:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.51,1:06:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.51,1:06:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.63,1:06:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.51,1:06:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.51,1:06:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.51,1:06:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.51,1:06:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.71,1:06:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.51,1:06:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.25,1:06:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.25,1:06:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.25,1:06:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.51,1:07:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.67,1:07:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NLet's go to the slides honey, the way we had them setup.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.71,1:07:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Using the scale of consciousness, then, we can re-confirm the presence of God and divinity of Jesus Christ.\NAnd that is how I got to correspond with Mother Teresa, hidden in the late 80's, I think it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.36,1:07:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.76,1:07:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.61,1:07:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.01,1:07:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.94,1:07:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.80,1:07:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a sort of a vociferous anti-God and anti-Jesus Christ.\NTime magazine or Life magazine came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.09,1:07:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Was Jesus Christ a schizophrenic?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.82,1:07:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, oh, okay, yes.\NYou still exist. I forgot you were still existing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.88,1:08:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so there was a doubt raised about the divinity of Jesus Christ.\NAnd using the scale of consciousness, this particular slide right here,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.68,1:08:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we reconfirmed the divinity of Jesus Christ.\NAnd so I thought Mother Teresa would be interested
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.67,1:08:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's confirmation of the divinity of Jesus Christ\Nthat does not depend on historical authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.03,1:09:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She probably thought questioning the divinity of Jesus was absurd,\Nbut the world was looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.98,1:09:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, I thought she would be interested\Nthat we found a way through consciousness research
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.90,1:09:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to affirm the divinity of Jesus Christ.\NMother Teresa would be interested in the divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.02,1:09:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother Teresa would be interested in the divinity of Jesus Christ.\NAnd so I thought that there was a doubt raised about the divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.06,1:09:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I thought that there was a doubt raised about the divinity of Jesus Christ.\NAnd so I thought that there was a doubt raised about the divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.22,1:09:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I thought that there was a doubt raised about the divinity of Jesus Christ.\NAnd so I thought that there was a doubt raised about the divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.28,1:09:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I thought that there was a doubt raised about the divinity of Jesus Christ.\NSo anyway, I don't know if she understood it, but she wrote me a nice note.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.67,1:10:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if Mother Teresa understood it, but she wrote me a nice note.\NShe probably thought doubting the divinity of Jesus Christ was absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.35,1:10:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But the world was being, you know, just like now in the state of Washington,\Nin the state of Washington and the rotunda of the Capitol,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.97,1:10:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of Christmas is being ridiculed, you know.\NAll right, so we thought the first thing we could do with this calibrated scale
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.10,1:11:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is reconfirm the great avatars and see what,\Ndoes the Buddha, what does the Buddha calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.64,1:11:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the Buddha, Jesus Christ, Krishna?\NSo, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.76,1:11:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the supreme states as we know them.\NGod manifests.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.68,1:11:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,God is manifest as all of creation.\NAnd then we have archangel.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.34,1:11:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the existence of the earth.\NThere is a god and a great angel that appears as a god and a creator.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.00,1:12:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, God could be unmanifest or manifest.\NAs you can see, the god may not appear or may appear.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.52,1:12:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The god may not appear or may appear.\NThe god may not appear or may appear.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.97,1:12:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The god may not appear or may appear.\NSo between divinity and our world,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.27,1:12:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there's like step-down transformer.\NStep-down transformer.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.52,1:12:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So between divinity and our world,\Nthere's like a step-down transformer.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.13,1:12:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo in our world,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.85,1:12:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there are acknowledged to be archangels.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.97,1:12:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to do what archangels have been.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.47,1:12:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.56,1:12:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.61,1:12:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.68,1:12:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.77,1:12:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.26,1:12:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.30,1:12:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.34,1:12:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels.\NArchangels.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.92,1:12:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangel calibrates 6,000 and over.\NAnd it was the Archangel that I experienced that brought me out of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.10,1:13:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NSo I myself experienced the Archangel calibrate to level 6,000 when I was in the pits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.23,1:13:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been in very exalted states.\NI've also been in the pits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.72,1:13:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not recommend the pits of hell.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.93,1:13:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up very religious and a very religious family.\NAnd my uncles, I had uncles that were bishops in the church, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.26,1:14:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And from that, eventually, due to the vicissitudes of life, it's a whole long story.\NI became an atheist for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.10,1:14:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And as an atheist,\NI had a drivenness to get to the core of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.97,1:14:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the truth, of truth itself, to get to the very core of out of which truth arises.\NAnd so I explored through inner meditation and dedication.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.44,1:15:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I searched for the core of the ego itself.\NIn searching for the roots of the ego itself, not as a concept, but as an experiential reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.89,1:15:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it led me into, eventually, the levels of hell.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.15,1:15:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.00,1:15:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.03,1:15:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.10,1:15:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.22,1:15:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.26,1:15:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.34,1:15:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.42,1:15:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.53,1:15:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.64,1:15:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.77,1:15:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.30,1:15:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.84,1:15:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.56,1:15:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NSo just as heaven and bliss and divinity is above, hell is below.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.06,1:15:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think of, as I have described in previous lectures, in exploring the depths of hell,\Nit was, they were pretty much, it was a very big thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.69,1:16:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty much as Dante envisioned them, Dante.\NAs I said in my previous lecture,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.88,1:16:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of hell is very similar to what Dante described.\NThe degree of agony increases beyond imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.73,1:16:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In the higher levels of hell, there is torture and dementia and savagery.\NBut that's just the top of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.53,1:16:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the good part of hell.\NThen it gets serious.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.69,1:17:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I kept going deeper and deeper.\NInto the source of hell, the levels of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.81,1:17:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember in the depths of hell,\Npassing a sign that said,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.43,1:17:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ye who enter here, give up all hope.\NAs I went down to hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.39,1:17:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard a sign that said,\NThose who pass through here, give up all hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.63,1:17:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember seeing that sign.\NWith some kind of incredibly, I don't know, demented dedication,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.60,1:17:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I proceeded to go into the depths of hell,\Nand I ignored the warning sign.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.89,1:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I ignored the sign and continued to go down.\NAbandon all hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.32,1:18:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ye who enter here, was the warning sign.\NAs I passed here,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.76,1:18:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I think in Dante's description of hell\NI think that occurs in Dante's
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.47,1:18:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Dante, D-A-N-T-E\Ndescription of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.85,1:18:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But there it was on the right side of me\Na sign, a warning sign
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.06,1:18:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandon all hope, ye who enter here\NSo then, driven by
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.77,1:18:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to say\Na dedication to truth and the extreme
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.72,1:19:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I ignored the sign and the warning\NAnd I went deeper and deeper
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.35,1:19:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,into hell\Nand reached hopelessness and despair
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.35,1:19:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and abandonment\NHopelessness and despair and abandonment
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.72,1:19:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I experienced despair forever\NAnd that level of despair
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.03,1:19:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and that level of hell\Nthere is agony forever
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.25,1:20:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that level of hell\Nyou understand what forever means
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.03,1:20:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As I speak, it is only a word to you\NBut in hell, there is agony forever
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.18,1:20:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that level of hell\Nyou experience eternity
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.77,1:20:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopeless despair forever\NThe agony not of the body
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.26,1:20:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,like the higher levels of hell\Nbut of the soul
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.03,1:20:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,at the lowest levels of hell\NThe agony not of the body
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.72,1:20:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,like the higher levels of hell\NYou experience the pain of death
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.50,1:21:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The agony of death\NAt the deepest levels of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.59,1:21:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I was there for eternity\NI was there for eternity
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.27,1:21:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I experienced it\NExperientially
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.72,1:21:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At last a thought came from within\NIf there is a God I ask Him for help
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.97,1:21:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an Atheist at the time\NI was an Atheist at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.02,1:21:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of my life, I was a dizendo\NAt the end of my life, I was a denial
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.00,1:21:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're an atheist\Nand find yourself pleading with God
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.68,1:21:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you know you've almost completed the trip.\NSo out of the totality of eternal despair
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.14,1:22:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,agony forever\Nagony forever
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.64,1:22:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a voice arose from within\Nand said
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.78,1:22:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God\NI ask him for help.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.85,1:22:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In the midst of eternal pain\Nin the midst of the whole of pain
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.43,1:22:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God\NI ask for help.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.96,1:22:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the voice that came up from within me.\NIt was an archangel that heard me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.68,1:22:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That archangel\Ncalibrated at 6,000
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.65,1:22:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an archangel\Nat calibration level 6,000
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.52,1:22:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,heard me\Nand must have given me a glance
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.84,1:23:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to be noticed\Nby an archangel
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.10,1:23:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,completely took me out of the depths of hell\Nand I went into a state
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.40,1:23:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of eternal ecstasy\Nand all that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.05,1:23:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,revealed itself as divinity.\NJust by looking at the archangel
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.05,1:23:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I got out of hell\Nand as a state of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.31,1:23:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I experienced everything that exists\Nas a peace of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.52,1:23:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That all exists\Nis God
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.18,1:23:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and infinitely perfect and beautiful\Nrevealed itself
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.27,1:23:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in a profound and stunning way.\NEverything that exists is God
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.77,1:23:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that exists is God\NLet's calibrate that extreme.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.38,1:23:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to pay attention to the actual reality\NYou just have to cover yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.38,1:23:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can see what God created\Nand it's all by God
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.47,1:23:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can saw goodness\Nand it's all beautiful
