Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.19,1:39:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,here's the black bear\Nthe jackal, the fox, the wolf
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.19,1:39:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hippopotamus\NThen we come to javelina
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.55,1:39:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You see we're below 200\NYou don't want to ignore these people
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.60,1:39:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because the hippopotamus kills more people\NI think than any other animal right now
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.60,1:39:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippopotamus\NAnd so below 200 you're in danger
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.60,1:39:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200 and up now you begin to see\Nthe emergence of that which is benign
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.76,1:39:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is voracious\NVoracious, the dinosaur is voracious
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.98,1:39:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And now at 200 suddenly you see a shift of energy\Nand you find those that stay alive by grazing
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.07,1:39:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You find the deer doesn't have to kill anybody\NThe bison doesn't kill anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.07,1:40:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They all eat grass\NEverybody here eats grass
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.07,1:40:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When in doubt eat grass\NSo below 200 there are animals that are very dangerous to humans
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.19,1:40:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and above 200 there are herbivorous animals\NSo now we move up the scale of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.19,1:40:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the way it's represented in the animal kingdom\NYou see the sheep are at 210
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.19,1:40:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Range cattle 210\NThe elephant at 235
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.23,1:40:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The elephant is relatively safe unless you cross him\Nand then he may squish you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.77,1:40:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you come to the farm horse\NAnd then the domestic cat 245
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.68,1:40:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And what?\NAnd then the race horses and dogs at 250
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.48,1:40:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The family dog\NAnd Kelsey our family dog calibrates at 255
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.10,1:41:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,255 resist\N256
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.52,1:41:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,255\N256
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.52,1:41:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we better send her back to school\NThe dog you're raising, Kelsey, is 265
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.52,1:41:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, being loving and around humans\NThe family dog will calibrate five points higher than a dog not with the family
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.52,1:41:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we get up to the gorilla at 275\NSome of these gorillas are very famous
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.52,1:41:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Very famous gorilla\NRemember there was a baby dropped into a pit where the gorilla lived
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.18,1:41:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A baby dropped over the edge\NAnd the gorilla came over and picked up the gorilla
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.18,1:41:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the gorilla came over and picked up the gorilla\NAnd the gorilla came over and picked up the gorilla
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.18,1:42:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And picked up the baby and brought it over\NAnd laid it gently by the gate
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.18,1:42:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,For the mother to come and get it\NI belong to the gorilla foundation
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.38,1:42:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You belong to the gorilla foundation?\NThat gorilla calibrated over 280, 290, 300
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.43,1:42:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,295, 300\NI forget the name of that gorilla
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.72,1:42:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget her name\NShe calibrates at 295
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.72,1:42:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,295\NI have her picture at home on the refrigerator
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.72,1:42:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the gorilla that she talks\NShe learns sign language
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.92,1:42:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco\NCoco the gorilla
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.96,1:42:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She learns sign language\NAnd I have a picture of her
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.96,1:43:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're holding a kitten\NAnd Coco is saying nice nice soft soft cat cat
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.39,1:43:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco the gorilla is saying nice nice soft soft cat cat\NNice nice soft soft cat cat
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.78,1:43:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how you begin to love the animals\NAs you yourself evolve
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.78,1:43:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You eventually love all these animals\NYou begin to love them
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.78,1:43:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the gorilla\NAnd you see the gorilla is caring for a child like its own, or a gorilla has a kitten.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.94,1:43:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice, nice, soft, soft, kitty, kitty.\NI've got a picture of the gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.32,1:43:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget her name.\NAnd she's got the kitty there, and she says, nice, nice, soft, soft, kitty, kitty.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.36,1:43:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice, nice, soft, soft, kitty, kitty.\NAnd then there's the famous cat, Oscar, who can tell when you're going to die within a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.59,1:44:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was famous in the paper.\NAnd if Oscar climbs in bed with you, it means you'll be dead within a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.39,1:44:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He was correct 23 out of 24 times, or no, 23 times in a row.\NHe was 23 times, all of them were correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.55,1:44:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the famous Alex, the gray parrot.\NWe have a gray parrot at home, and very talky.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.46,1:44:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What's her name?\NBroccoli.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.67,1:44:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got a parrot name, Broccoli, which means very talkative.\NWe have permission to calibrate Broccoli.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.64,1:44:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli is over 400, 405, 402.\NAnyway, we have an African gray parrot at home that was a gift from a friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.13,1:45:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And she talks up a storm, talks to the dog.\NWhat's the dog's name?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.39,1:45:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelsey.\NSo the bird will say, Kelsey, Kelsey, come here, come here, come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.34,1:45:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the dog runs over.\NIn a jealous way, you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.81,1:45:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Imitating your voice, then.\NIn my voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.92,1:45:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, she goes, the dog runs over.\NThe dog runs over, and then she goes, get away from that bird.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.32,1:46:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.\NSo you see how as they come up, we begin to relate to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.85,1:46:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to love the animals.\NAnd I think one of the best presents you can give a kid is a kitty or a puppy or something to be responsible for.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.59,1:46:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But we begin to love the animals.\NBecause they're up in 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.51,1:46:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if you love the deer, we love the elk and the deer.\NBut now you get up higher, and you really finally reach Coco, the trained gorilla, is at 405.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.36,1:46:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize you're safer in a cage with this gorilla than you are with about 90% of mankind.\NThe fact that we're all like this gorilla is safer than being with 95%, 85% of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.34,1:46:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's safer.\NThen we come up to the songbird's song, and then very profoundly, the cat's purr, 500, the dog's wagging tail, 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.38,1:47:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,굉장히 심오하게도 고양이의 가라랑거리는 소리와 개의 꼬리 흔들기는 500으로 측정됩니다.\NSo people say, well, you just imagine that the dog loves you, or that the kitty loves you,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.42,1:47:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but when we calibrate it and the kitty's purring, that's 500.\NIt's not our imagination. The kitty is loving you.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.57,1:47:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,당신은 개가 당신을 사랑한다고 상상하지만 실제로\NAnd the dog's wagging tail is love.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.52,1:47:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,개는 실제로 당신을 사랑합니다. 왜냐하면 개의 꼬리 흔들기가 500으로, 사랑의 수준은 500으로 측정되기 때문입니다.\NThere was some advertiser that recently discovered that by putting a dog's wagging tail in their advertisement on television, they quadruple their sales.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.71,1:47:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,광고에 꼬리 흔드는 개의 사진을\N광고에 꼬리 흔드는 개의 사진을
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.10,1:47:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,올려서 판매가 3배로 올랐답니다.\NSo if you're having trouble with somebody in your life, try wagging your tail.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.65,1:48:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,당신이 살면서 누구와 문제가 있다면 당신의 꼬리를 살짝 흔들어 주세요.\NOkay, the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.93,1:48:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is a little more sophisticated.\N이거는 조금 더 복잡한 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.21,1:48:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In every situation, there is...\Nthere's the content and there's an infinite field and approximate field.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.60,1:48:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is local and this is overall.\N어떤 상황에도 콘텐츠가 있고 무한한 장과 근접한, 조금 더 근접한 장이 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.34,1:48:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So a definable truth has to be defined in what situation and under what circumstances a certain thing is true.\NSo a definable truth has to be defined in what situation and under what circumstances a certain thing is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.47,1:49:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to distinguish between two events, it is important to know the context and the situation in which the event takes place.\NSo the universe is in a state of infinite potentiality, and then through the Heisenberg process, by our intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.09,1:50:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we collapse the wave function, and that which is potential becomes infinite.\NAll right, so the great discovery was that human consciousness, that intention, can make things manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.19,1:50:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you have potential.\NAnd now by our intention, by our free will, we make them actually happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.22,1:50:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that's the basis of the test that we do.\NNow, she does not know.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.53,1:51:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She does not know what I'm holding in mind.\NShe had no way to know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.50,1:51:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no possible linear explanation.\NSo what happens is that we collapse the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:26.07,1:51:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say what I'm holding in mind calibrates over 200,\NIf it's not a fact, it has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.15,1:51:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If it has no reality, it cannot cause your arm to go strong.\NIf I hold in mind, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.17,1:52:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The wave function only collapses if it's based on truth.\NThe reason is, it has no existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.51,1:52:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is false has no existence.\NSo if I say to her, what I'm holding in mind calibrates such and such.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.47,1:52:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,For the arm to go strong, there has to be a concordance between truth and her arm.\NHer arm is responding to...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.64,1:52:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,...the energy of the truth itself.\NFor it to be more than 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.85,1:52:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're thinking about in your head\Nhas to be in harmony with the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.21,1:53:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I still didn't explain it well.\NThat which is true has existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.48,1:53:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is true is.\NThat which is true is.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.85,1:53:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not really a test of true versus false.\NIt's a test of existence versus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.69,1:53:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.\NIf I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.07,1:53:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.\NIf I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.19,1:53:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.\NIf I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.23,1:53:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.\NIf I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.38,1:53:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.\NIf I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.43,1:53:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If I make a false statement, it has no existence and no reality.\NIf I make a false accusation, it doesn't exist and it doesn't exist in reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:46.94,1:53:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist.\NIt doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.35,1:54:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't exist, then her arm goes weak.\NSo it's not yes versus no.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.40,1:54:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not yes, not yes.\NIt's is versus is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.23,1:54:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I say Hitler calibrates over 200.\NHitler calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:30.02,1:54:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no reality.\NI say Hitler calibrated below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.73,1:54:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no reality.\NHitler calibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.26,1:54:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not a test of yes and no or true and false.\NIt's a test of what is versus what is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.35,1:55:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What is makes your arm go strong.\NHitler calibrated about 70, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.82,1:55:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I will ask that.\NWe have permission to do Hitler.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:07.90,1:55:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He calibrated about 70, 75.\NSo the fact that he holds 70 in mind has a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:16.68,1:55:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it has no reality, it doesn't exist in reality.\NAnd because it has no reality, it doesn't exist in reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.18,1:55:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it has no reality, it doesn't exist in reality.\NAnd because it has no reality, it doesn't exist in reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.11,1:55:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She has the energy to go strong.\NSo it's not a test of yes versus no, or true versus false.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.81,1:55:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really a test of what is versus what is not.\NWhich is understandable by the quantum mechanics, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.19,1:55:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you explained.\NWhat did I say anyway? I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.18,1:55:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's true that Hitler car throttle is below 70,\Nand it makes his arm go strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.10,1:55:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why.\NSo this is.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.18,1:55:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is.\NAnd this is.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.27,1:56:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes or no is not yes or no, it's either yes or no, because the truth is real, so it's either yes or no, not yes or no.\NSo what we call kundalini spiritual energy begins to flow up the spinal column through the various chakras.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:43.55,1:57:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the lower levels of energy energize this side of the brain, the higher levels of energy energize this side of the brain.\NSo below level 200, the level of falsehood, the world you see is linear, left brain, and fight or flight and stress.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.42,1:57:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the muscle goes up.\NThe muscle goes weak, the test response is weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.96,1:57:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the neurotransmitters in the brain are different.\NYou see, you're pouring out adrenaline because you're all ready for fight or flight.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.10,1:58:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Above consciousness level 200, the brain, people's brain operates differently.\NRight brain, yeah, above 200 is right brain, dominance.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:04.34,1:58:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the kundalini energy flows up and energizes the right side of the brain.\N200 or more, the right brain is dominant, and the kundalini energy goes up the spine and activates the right brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:18.19,1:58:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so this releases adrenaline, fight or flight.\NThis is adrenaline, fight or flight.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:26.93,1:58:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight or flight.\NAnd this releases adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.23,1:58:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Endorphins.\NEndorphins, positive emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.46,1:58:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And that brings about healing.\NAnd a balance of the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:51.18,1:58:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo a person who has a benign view of life, their brain works differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:58.03,1:59:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd their hormone system works differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:07.56,1:59:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't mean that this is immutable, but it takes a lot more.\NRight above 200, it takes a great deal more to cause a human problem or an illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.03,1:59:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.96,1:59:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.06,1:59:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.35,1:59:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.43,1:59:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.56,1:59:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\Nand so one's health improves but only to a certain level and beyond that you have to do with karma and we don't have karma on the chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:48.06,2:00:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So one's health improves but only to a certain level and beyond that you have to do with karma.\NSo one's health improves but only to a certain level and beyond that you have to do with karma and we don't have karma on the chart.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:40.71,2:00:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,During the Great Depression I always had a job.\NIn fact I had two jobs.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:56.47,2:01:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact I had two jobs.\NOn the way home from the two jobs I sold various things so I really had three jobs.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:02.47,2:01:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,My rate of unemployment was zero.\NMoney was tight but I eluded poverty.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:14.57,2:01:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that I was surviving, life was okay.\NThis is very important sociologically
Dialogue: 0,2:01:33.02,2:01:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and politically.\NThis is very important sociologically and politically.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:36.02,2:01:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the politician says if we do this or that we will change this.\NBecause the politician says if we do this or that we will change this.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:47.10,2:01:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't change it.\NBut you can change the likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:58.10,2:02:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But even under the best of circumstances many people will go wrong.\NBut even under the best of circumstances many people will go wrong.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:06.10,2:02:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And other people, under terrible circumstances, manage to survive.\NAnd other people, under terrible circumstances, manage to survive.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:16.10,2:02:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So what keeps us alive is our good will towards ourselves and our fellow men.\NWhich keeps us alive is our good will towards ourselves and our fellow men.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:31.72,2:02:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're going to kill him, kill him because you love him.\NRelieve you of your earthly burdens.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:41.60,2:02:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, God bless.\NWe're going to break, and we'll be back at what time?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:46.42,2:02:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Back at 2 o'clock.\NThank you.
